Hynix Semiconductor’s Shares Rise in Seoul After Memory Chip Prices Climb

-- B y   J u n   Y a n g
-- 
2011-08-29T00:19:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-29/hynix-semiconductor-s-shares-rise-in-seoul-after-memory-chip-prices-climb.html
Hynix Semiconductor Inc. (000660)  gained as
much as 4.2 percent in Seoul trading after computer-memory chip
prices rose. Shares in Hynix traded up 2.8 percent to 18,450 won
as of 9:13 a.m., while the benchmark Kospi index climbed 1.2
percent. The price of the benchmark DDR3 2-gigabit DRAM rose 3.1
percent Friday, according to data from Taipei- based
Dramexchange Technology Inc., operator of  Asia ’s largest spot
market for semiconductors.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jun Yang in Seoul at 
 jyang180@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shinhye Kang at 
 skang24@bloomberg.net  